<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Key G, 4/4. "33" root triads and "43" inversions throughout. LH full 4-note open voicings.
- Eb in bar 6 substituted with Am (②m) then G (①) — nearest diatonic neighbours.
- F#° substituted as D (⑤) — dominant function preserved.
- Am7 rendered as ②m throughout.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- LH E2 common tone through Am and Em passages.
- RH descends stepwise across final cadence (A5→D5→G4).

TEXTURE ARC:
- Short 8-bar hymn. Opens 3-voice LH, fills out bar 5-6 with upper treble extension.
- Final G cadence: full root-position close.
-->
